{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 10''' is the 10th day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引}} .
== Events == * {{ill|Keiun|ja|慶雲}} 1 ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|June 16|ja|6月16日}} , {{ill|704|ja|704th year}} ) - The era name changed from {{ill|Taihō|ja|大宝}} to Keiun due to auspicious cloud omens. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久}} 3 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}} {{ill|June 25|ja|6月25日}} , {{ill|1863|ja|1863rd year}} ) - {{ill|Chōshū Domain|ja|Chōshū Domain}} fired upon American merchant ships anchored in the {{ill|Shimonoseki Strait|ja|下関海峡}} . * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 4 (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日}} , {{ill|1871|ja|1871st year}} ) - The {{ill|New Currency Act|ja|新貨条例}} was promulgated, adopting the decimal system and establishing "yen, sen, and rin" as currency units. The old 1 ryo was set equal to 1 yen.
== Births == * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化}} 3 (Intercalary May) (Gregorian calendar {{ill|July 3|ja|7月3日}} , {{ill|1846|ja|1846th year}} ) - {{ill|Princess Kazunomiya|ja|和宮親子内親王}} , eighth daughter of {{ill|Emperor Ninkō|ja|仁孝天皇}} and wife of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemochi|ja|徳川家茂}} (+ {{ill|1877|ja|1877th year}} ). == Deaths == * {{ill|Emperor Suizei|ja|綏靖天皇}} 33 (Julian calendar {{ill|June 10|ja|6月10日}} , {{ill|549 BC|ja|紀元前549th year}} ) - {{ill|Emperor Suizei|ja|綏靖天皇}} , 2nd {{ill|Emperor of Japan|ja|天皇}} . == See Also ==
