{{Lunisolar May|qq=}} 
'''May 10''' is the 10th day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} . 

== Events ==
* {{ill|Keiun|ja|慶雲|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  1 ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|June 16|ja|6月16日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|704|ja|704th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) - The era name changed from {{ill|Taihō|ja|大宝|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  to Keiun due to auspicious cloud omens.
* {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  3 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  {{ill|June 25|ja|6月25日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|1863|ja|1863rd year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) - {{ill|Chōshū Domain|ja|Chōshū Domain|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  fired upon American merchant ships anchored in the {{ill|Shimonoseki Strait|ja|下関海峡|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  4 (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|1871|ja|1871st year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) - The {{ill|New Currency Act|ja|新貨条例|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  was promulgated, adopting the decimal system and establishing "yen, sen, and rin" as currency units. The old 1 ryo was set equal to 1 yen.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  3 (Intercalary May) (Gregorian calendar {{ill|July 3|ja|7月3日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|1846|ja|1846th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) - {{ill|Princess Kazunomiya|ja|和宮親子内親王|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , eighth daughter of {{ill|Emperor Ninkō|ja|仁孝天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  and wife of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemochi|ja|徳川家茂|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  (+ {{ill|1877|ja|1877th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Emperor Suizei|ja|綏靖天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}}  33 (Julian calendar {{ill|June 10|ja|6月10日|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , {{ill|549 BC|ja|紀元前549th year|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} ) - {{ill|Emperor Suizei|ja|綏靖天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} , 2nd {{ill|Emperor of Japan|ja|天皇|qq=|12=draft|12=draft}} .
