== Events == * {{ill|Keiun|ja|慶雲|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Keiun|qq=}} 1 ( {{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Julian calendar|qq=}} {{ill|June 16|ja|6月16日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 16|qq=}} , {{ill|704|ja|704年|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/704|qq=}} ) - The era name changed from {{ill|Taihō|ja|大宝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taihō|qq=}} to Keiun due to auspicious cloud omens. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunkyū|qq=}} 3 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Gregorian calendar|qq=}} {{ill|June 25|ja|6月25日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 25|qq=}} , {{ill|1863|ja|1863年|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1863|qq=}} ) - {{ill|Chōshū Domain|ja|Chōshū Domain|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōshū Domain|qq=}} fired upon American merchant ships anchored in the {{ill|Shimonoseki Strait|ja|下関海峡|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimonoseki Strait|qq=}} . * {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 4 (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/June 27|qq=}} , {{ill|1871|ja|1871年|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1871|qq=}} ) - The {{ill|New Currency Act|ja|新貨条例|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Currency Act|qq=}} was promulgated, adopting the decimal system and establishing "yen, sen, and rin" as currency units. The old 1 ryo was set equal to 1 yen.
