'''May 10''' is the 10th day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May (Satsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May (Lunisolar)|qq=}}  the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}}  day is {{ill|Tomobiki|qid=Q96759840|1=tomobiki}}{{efn|ja|友引|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomobiki|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}} . 

== Events ==
* {{ill|Keiun|en|Keiun|qid=Q428753|lt=Keiun|1=Keiun}}  1 ( {{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}}  {{ill|June 16|en|June 16|qid=Q2653|lt=June 16|1=June 16}} , {{ill|704|en|704|qid=Q23503|lt=704|1=704}} ) - The era name changed from {{ill|Taiho|en|Taiho|qid=Q423370|lt=Taihō|1=Taiho}}  to Keiun due to auspicious cloud omens.
* {{ill|Bunkyū|en|Bunkyū|qid=Q730266|lt=Bunkyū|1=Bunkyū}}  3 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}}  {{ill|June 25|en|June 25|qid=Q2662|lt=June 25|1=June 25}} , {{ill|1863|en|1863|qid=Q7701|lt=1863|1=1863}} ) - {{ill|Chōshū Domain|1=Chōshū Domain|2=ja|3=長州藩|ja|Chōshū Domain|1=Chōshū Domain|2=ja|3=長州藩|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chōshū Domain|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q876267}}  fired upon American merchant ships anchored in the {{ill|Shimonoseki Strait|ja|下関海峡|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimonoseki Strait|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 関門海峡|1=Kanmon Straits|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q494894}} .
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|qid=Q3125096|lt=Meiji era|1=Meiji era}}  4 (Gregorian calendar {{ill|June 27|en|June 27|qid=Q2664|lt=June 27|1=June 27}} , {{ill|1871|en|1871|qid=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}} ) - The {{ill|New Currency Act|ja|新貨条例|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Currency Act|1=New Currency Act|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11504131}}  was promulgated, adopting the decimal system and establishing "yen, sen, and rin" as currency units. The old 1 ryo was set equal to 1 yen.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kōka|en|Kōka|qid=Q1325317|lt=Kōka|1=Kōka}}  3 (Intercalary May) (Gregorian calendar {{ill|July 3|en|July 3|qid=Q2699|lt=July 3|1=July 3}} , {{ill|1846|en|1846|qid=Q7640|lt=1846|1=1846}} ) - {{ill|Chikako, Princess Kazu|en|Chikako, Princess Kazu|qid=Q907048|lt=Princess Kazunomiya|1=Chikako, Princess Kazu}} , eighth daughter of {{ill|Emperor Ninkō|en|Emperor Ninkō|qid=Q312351|lt=Emperor Ninkō|1=Emperor Ninkō}}  and wife of {{ill|Tokugawa Iemochi|en|Tokugawa Iemochi|qid=Q348466|lt=Tokugawa Iemochi|1=Tokugawa Iemochi}}  (+ {{ill|1877|en|1877|qid=Q7773|lt=1877|1=1877}} ).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Emperor Suizei|en|Emperor Suizei|qid=Q313321|lt=Emperor Suizei|1=Emperor Suizei}}  33 (Julian calendar {{ill|June 10|en|June 10|qid=Q2615|lt=June 10|1=June 10}} , {{ill|549 BC|en|549 BC|qid=Q243600|lt=549 BC|1=549 BC}} ) - {{ill|Emperor Suizei|en|Emperor Suizei|qid=Q313321|lt=Emperor Suizei|1=Emperor Suizei}} , 2nd {{ill|Emperor of Japan|en|Emperor of Japan|qid=Q208233|lt=Emperor of Japan|1=Emperor of Japan}} .

